      • isPvPDisabledForPlayers

        public int isPvPDisabledForPlayers(org.bukkit.entity.Player playerGettingHurt,
                                   org.bukkit.entity.Player playerCausingHarm)
        This will check if the specific players have PVP disabled.
        Parameters:
        playerGettingHurt - This will be the player that's currently being attacked
        playerCausingHarm - This will be the player that's doing the attacking.
        Returns:
        1 - Cancelled - Both players have PvP Disabled.
        2 - Cancelled - The player that is getting hurt has PvP Disabled.
        3 - Cancelled - The player that is causing harm has it disabled.
        4 - Allowed - The player causing harm is OP and can bypass.
        0 - Allowed - Allows the PvP to go on as normal.
